<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">318. Dyer, Anne. Dyes from Natural Sources. London: G. Bell, 1976. 88 pp. Index, B/W illus. ISBN 0-7135-1937-1. </p><p class="annot">This book covers all aspects of dyeing wool, including the art of testdyeing. A special feature is the section on dyeing in schoolrooms. Plants in Britain, North America, Australia, and New Zealand are described though not illustrated. Although it has an instructive text, the book has only one black and white drawing in each chapter. </p></div>
